<b>Alan M. Frieze</b> is a professor in the Department of Mathematical Sciences at <university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../093/48093.xml">
Carnegie Mellon University</link></university>
, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../101/25101.xml">
Pittsburgh</link>, United States. He graduated
from the <university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../797/31797.xml">
University of Oxford</link></university>
 in 1966, and obtained his PhD from the <university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../919/60919.xml">
University of London</link></university>
 in 1975. He currently works in the areas of <link>
probabilistic combinatorics</link> and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../477/358477.xml">
random graphs</link>. In 1991 he was a co-recipient of the <symbol wordnetid="106806469" confidence="0.8">
<award wordnetid="106696483" confidence="0.8">
<signal wordnetid="106791372" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../916/1425916.xml">
Fulkerson Prize</link></signal>
</award>
</symbol>
 (with <link>
Martin E. Dyer</link> and <physical_entity wordnetid="100001930" confidence="0.8">
<person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.8">
<causal_agent wordnetid="100007347" confidence="0.8">
<scientist wordnetid="110560637" confidence="0.8">
<mathematician wordnetid="110301261" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../339/6227339.xml">
Ravindran Kannan</link></mathematician>
</scientist>
</causal_agent>
</person>
</physical_entity>
) for his paper "A random polynomial-time algorithm for approximating the volume of convex bodies". He was also a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../430/1554430.xml">
Guggenheim Fellow</link> in 1997.
